Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 7. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Pour enough @oil{} into a deep #baking tray{} to cover the bottom and pop into the oven. Peel the @potatoes{450%g}, then chop into 3cm chunks.

Remove the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from the fridge to come up to room temperature before cooking.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Boil the potatoes for ~{5-6%minutes} or until the edges are soft.

Chop the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{}. Sprinkle on the @plain flour{1%tbsp}, @dried rosemary{1} and season with @salt{}. Shake to fluff up the potatoes.

Take your hot baking tray out of your oven and carefully add the potatoes, turning in the oil. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a small #bowl{}, mix together the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing with the @red wine vinegar{2%tbsp} and half the @wholegrain mustard{1/2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Add the tomatoes to the dressing. Toss to coat and set aside.

When the potatoes have 15 mins remaining, add a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, about ~{1%minute} ~{15%seconds} on each side.

> Cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. They're safe to eat when browned on the outside.

Return the (now empty) saucepan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle more oil if needed.

Fry the garlic for ~{1%minute}, then stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @water{50%ml} and the remaining wholegrain mustard.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

When the potatoes have 5 mins left, remove the tray from the oven and sprinkle over the @Parmigiano Reggiano{20%g}. Return to the oven and roast for the remaining time.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the @wild rocket{40%g} with the tomatoes.

Transfer your steaks to your plates and serve with your parmesan roasties and salad alongside.

Spoon over the creamy mustard sauce to finish. Enjoy!